}
```

This command uses the `npx` command to run the `playwright-test` command, which is the Playwright test runner.

4. Once you've added the `test` command to your `project.json` file, you can run the Playwright test runner by using the following command in your terminal:

* For npm: `npm run test`
* For yarn: `yarn run test`

This will run the Playwright test runner using the default configuration. If you need to customize the configuration, you can specify command line options or create a `playwright.config.js` file. You can find more information about configuring the Playwright test runner in the [Playwright documentation](https://playwright.dev/docs/test-runner).

