To create a drag-and-drop Kanban board in React, you can use a library called `react-dnd` (React Drag and Drop). Here's a step-by-step guide to create a simple Kanban board:

1. Install `react-dnd` and `react-dnd-html5-backend` packages:

```bash
npm install react-dnd react-dnd-html5-backend
```

2. Create a new React app or use an existing one. Let's assume you have a project structure like this:

```
src
|-- components
|   |-- Column.js
|   |-- Card.js
|-- App.js
```

3. Create the `Card` component (src/components/Card.js):

```jsx
import React from 'react';
import { useDrag } from 'react-dnd';

const Card = ({ id, text }) => {
  const [{ isDragging }, drag] = useDrag(() => ({
    type: 'card',
    item: { id },
    collect: (monitor) => ({
      isDragging: !!monitor.isDragging(),
    }),
  }));

  return (
    <div
      ref={drag}
      style={{
        opacity: isDragging ? 0.5 : 1,
        border: '1px solid #000',
        borderRadius: 5,
        padding: 10,
        marginBottom: 10,
      }}
    >
      {text}
    </div>
  );
};

export default Card;
```

4. Create the `Column` component (src/components/Column.js):

```jsx
import React from 'react';
import Card from './Card';
import { useDrop } from 'react-dnd';

const Column = ({ title, cards, onMoveCard }) => {
  const [{ isOver }, drop] = useDrop(() => ({
    accept: 'card',
    drop: (item) => onMoveCard(item.id, title),
    collect: (monitor) => ({
      isOver: !!monitor.isOver(),
    }),
  }));

  return (
    <div
      ref={drop}
      style={{
        flexGrow: 1,
        margin: '0 10px',
        padding: 20,
        backgroundColor: isOver ? '#e0e0e0' : '#f0f0f0',
        borderRadius: 5,
      }}
    >
      <h3>{title}</h3>
      {cards.map((card) => (
        <Card key={card.id} id={card.id} text={card.text} />
      ))}
    </div>
  );
};

export default Column;
```

5. Update the `App` component (src/App.js):

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import Column from './components/Column';

const initialData = {
  columns: {
    'column-1': { id: 'column-1', title: 'To do', cards: [{ id: 'card-1', text: 'Task 1' }] },
    'column-2': { id: 'column-2', title: 'In Progress', cards: [{ id: 'card-2', text: 'Task 2' }] },
  },
  /* extra data you might want to add */
};

function App() {
  const [data, setData] = useState(initialData);

  const moveCard = (id, targetColumn) => {
    const sourceColumn = data.columns[id.split('-')[0]];
    const sourceCard = sourceColumn.cards.find((card) => card.id === id);

    if (!sourceCard) return;

    const newColumnOrder = { ...data.columnOrder };
    newColumnOrder.splice(newColumnOrder.indexOf(id.split('-')[0]), 1);
    newColumnOrder.splice(newColumnOrder.indexOf(targetColumn), 0, id.split('-')[0]);

    setData((prevData) => ({
      ...prevData,
      columns: {
        ...prevData.columns,
        [targetColumn]: {
          ...prevData.columns[targetColumn],
          cards: [...prevData.columns[targetColumn].cards, sourceCard],
        },
        [id.split('-')[0]]: {
          ...prevData.columns[id.split('-')[0]],
          cards: prevData.columns[id.split('-')[0]].cards.filter((card) => card.id !== id),
        },
      },
      columnOrder: newColumnOrder,
    }));
  };

  return (
    <div style={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'space-around' }}>
      {data.columnOrder.map((columnId) => (
        <Column
          key={columnId}
          title={data.columns[columnId].title}
          cards={data.columns[columnId].cards}
          onMoveCard={moveCard}
        />
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

Now you should have a simple drag-and-drop Kanban board in React. You can extend this example by adding more features like adding and deleting columns and cards, restricting the movement of cards based on certain conditions, etc.

