const url = window.location.href;

// Send a message to the background script with the title and URL.
chrome.runtime.sendMessage({ title, url });
```
This `content.js` file defines the following code:

* Get the title and URL of the current tab.
* Send a message to the background script with the title and URL.

Popup Folder
