APIs and Endpoints
-----------------

Our Task Manager extension uses the following APIs and endpoints:

* `chrome.tabs`: The Chrome tabs API allows our extension to interact with the tabs in the user's browser.
	+ `chrome.tabs.onCreated`: An event triggered when a new tab is created.
	+ `chrome.tabs.onUpdated`: An event triggered when a tab is updated.
	+ `chrome.tabs.onRemoved`: An event triggered when a tab is removed.
	+ `chrome.tabs.reload`: A method to reload a tab.
	+ `chrome.tabs.remove`: A method to remove a tab.
* `chrome.runtime`: The Chrome runtime API provides runtime services for a background script or extension page.
	+ `chrome.runtime.sendMessage`: A method to send a message from a content script to the background script.
	+ `chrome.runtime.onMessage`: An event triggered when a message is received by the background script.
* `chrome.storage`: The Chrome storage API provides storage for extension data.
	+ `chrome.storage.local`: A storage area for data that is persisted across browser sessions.

