Conclusion
----------

In this guide, we've learned how to build a basic Chrome extension called Task Manager. We've covered the different parts of a Chrome extension, such as the manifest file, service workers, content scripts, and popups. Additionally, we've explored some of the APIs and endpoints that can be used to build more advanced features into our extension. This guide should serve as a starting point for building your own Chrome extensions, and we encourage you to continue learning and experimenting with new ideas. Happy developing!

