                fail = 9

                if (ok) {
                    # Simulate LDAP response after MFA
                    update reply {
                        Reply-Message := "Multi-factor authentication succeeded"
                        Service-Type := Framed-User
                        Framed-Protocol := PPP
                        Framed-IP-Address := coa:Framed-IP-Address
                    }
                } else {
                    fail
                }
            }
        } else if (Auth-Type == "BSA") {
            bsa
        } else {
            # Handle "Reject" and other Auth-Types here if needed
        }
    } else {
        # Handle the failure case here
    }
    # Other post-auth logic
}
```

For the MFA responses, I assume that you have a way to determine if MFA has succeeded or failed. Modify the `if (ok)` condition for MFA in the `post-auth` section based on how your MFA modules return success or failure.

Remember to restart the FreeRADIUS service after making these changes.

This configuration assumes that the MFA module will update the `ok` variable based on authentication success or failure. If it does not, you will need to modify the `if (ok)` condition according to the MFA module's documentation or behavior. By following this structure, you should be able to configure FreeRADIUS to wait for MFA before granting access.

